> Another work day, another dinner daydream. You know what we mean. You're sitting at your desk and 2:00 p.m. rolls around. Suddenly, all you can think is, "Dinner...what the heck am I going to eat for dinner?!" Well, we've got you covered, and FYI, the answer to that question is pretty darn delicious. We're serving up succulent beef tenderloin with roasted green beans and savory couscous. To finish things off, the beef is drizzled with a life-affirming creamy dill sauce. Talk about a dream come true!

== Roasted Beef Tenderloin and Green Beans ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Line a #baking sheet{} with foil. Wash and dry produce.

Trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary. Pick and roughly chop fronds from @dill{1/4%ounce}.

Pat @beef tenderloin filets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{1%tablespoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add beef and sear, turning occasionally, until browned all over, ~{4-8%minutes} (it'll finish cooking in the next step).

Turn off heat; transfer beef to one side of prepared baking sheet.

> Swap in chicken or beef for pork. Cook chicken until browned and cooked through, 3-5 minutes per side, or cook beef to desired doneness, 4-7 minutes per side. Transfer to a cutting board to rest (skip the baking sheet––no need to roast!).

Add green beans to empty side of baking sheet; toss with a drizzle of olive oil, salt, pepper, and @chili flakes{1%teaspoon} to taste.

Roast on top rack until green beans are tender and beef is cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Remove from oven; transfer beef to a #cutting board{} to rest for ~{5%minutes}.

> Roast green beans without chicken or beef.

== Couscous ==

Meanwhile, add @Israeli couscous{2.5%ounce} and @butter{1%tablespoon} to a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Cook, stirring, until butter has melted and couscous is lightly toasted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @water{3/4%cup}, @chicken stock concentrate{1%unit}, and a big pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until couscous is tender, ~{6-8%minutes}.

> Drain excess water if necessary.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Creamy Dill Sauce ==

While couscous cooks, heat pan used for beef over medium-high heat. Add remaining @chicken stock concentrate{1%unit} and @water{1/4%cup}; bring to a simmer and cook ~{1-2%minutes}.

Reduce heat to low and whisk in @sour cream{3%tablespoon}, half the chopped dill, and @Dijon mustard{2%teaspoon} to taste. Turn off heat. Stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} and any resting juices from beef. Season with salt and pepper.

== To Serve ==

Fluff couscous with a fork and season with salt and pepper.

Slice beef crosswise.

Divide couscous, beef, and green beans between plates. Spoon sauce over beef and sprinkle with remaining chopped dill and any remaining chili flakes to taste. Serve.

> Slice chicken or beef against the grain.

> Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.